    "Evaluation": {
      "text": "Generally considered a diagnosis of exclusion after evaluating for other causes of\nnausea and vomiting",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Management": {
      "text": "Cessation of marijuana use, as hyperemetic phase lasts only 24-48 hrs unless pt relapses\nSymptomatic treatment (\nAntiemetics\n, anxiolytics, and hydration)\nHaloperidol\n5 mg IV/IM and\ndiphenhydramine\n50 mg IV\n[4]\nHot shower (>109°F), though short-lived\n[5]\nCapsaicin\ncream 0.025-0.075% across abdomen/arms/back, with symptoms diminishing within 30 min\n[6]\nLorazepam\n1-2 mg IV\n[7]",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Disposition": {
      "text": "Discharge once tolerating PO",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
